The article discusses the importance of everyone participating in democracy and the need to protect the right to vote. It calls for the Senate to pass the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act. The President and Vice President are using all available tools to promote voting access, including an executive order issued by President Biden in March 2021. Federal agencies have submitted strategic plans on how they plan to promote voting access, and the President and Vice President will ensure these plans are fully implemented. They are committed to working with these agencies to make voting accessible for all Americans.